CatDescriptText: Myrtle McDaniel, 7606 Mulford Street, Republican, 13th Ward minority inspector of election, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 7, 1957, pg. 3 with question: "Who is your Ward Chairman? Does he have any power? Does he exert it?" Answer reads: "Yes, our ward chairman is Mr. Durzo. I don't know whether or not he has power because I don't know of anything that he has got done.  If he gets that alley paved in rear of the 7600 block Mulford St., I'll say that he has power."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Myrtle McDaniel wearing eyeglasses and light colored dress standing next to car on residential street
